What if I have COVID-19?

Authority will make separate living arrangements for you or admit you to a hospital. They will monitor your health, whether it is improving or not. X-ray or blood test may also be needed. COVID-19 may make you and your family worried. However, 80% of the time, COVID-19 infections are mild. They do not even need any treatment. There is a slight risk of damage to those who are old or have other health problems. Only 5% of patients need ICU for helping them breathe.
